Reasoning: The paper deals with formalizing computational systems using logics that support fixed-point definitions, which is a topic that falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper introduces a natural deduction calculus that adds a form of "closed-world" equality to deduction modulo, a framework for extending a logic with a rewriting layer operating on formulas. This connects the paper to the sub-categories of programming languages (cs.PL), software engineering (cs.SE), formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL), and logic in computer science (cs.LG).
